      <chapter eId="chp_319o">
        <num>319o</num>
        <heading>Personal Care Assistance</heading>
        <section eId="sec_17b_31">
          <num>17b-31</num>
          <heading>Parent's Fair Share Program</heading>
          <subsection eId="17b_31__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The Commissioner of Social Services shall seek a waiver from federal law to participate in the federal Parent's Fair Share Program, Section 482</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="17b_31__subsec_d">
            <num>(d)</num>
            <paragraph eId="17b_31__subsec_d__subsec_3">
              <num>(3)</num>
              <content>
                <p>of the Social Security Act. Such program shall assist noncustodial parents in becoming current in delinquent child support payments.</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="17b_31__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The Commissioner of Social Services may accept private foundation grants and may use such grants to carry out the purposes of this section.
(Return to ChapterTable of Contents)(Return toList of Chapters)(Return toList of Titles)</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
